originalText.text: Cindy was absolutely amazing and lovely during my first visit, giving me great advice and information about gums retreats for next appointment. She made sure that I was comfortable during x-rays. Amazing team and professional. Thank you.

originalText.text: The dentist made an ER temporary repair of 2 chipped teeth, and only charged us for 1!  Her handiwork is great, she put the patient at ease, explained everything we needed to do for a permanent fix, and recommended we visit urgent care for other face injuries.  (From urgent care, we ended up being referred to the ER for a CT scan.)  She was helpful in every way, and we're so glad Tend fit us in.

originalText.text: I got my wisdom teeth out by Dr. Chen and he was very nice, especially cause I was a bit nervous— the procedure was super quick and I barely felt a thing!! they explain everything really clearly and answered all my questions. Also the office is really clean and comfy :)

originalText.text:
I visited for the first time today and unfortunately had the worst experience I’ve ever had at a dentist’s office before.

My hygienist seemed very flustered and confused. She spent little to no time cleaning my teeth and most of the time being flustered with the room setup and machines. When she did clean my teeth, she was rough and caused me to yelp at multiple moments. She also remarked that I “didn’t seem interested” in learning about the ladder of dental hygiene (but which she couldn’t remember the letters/words for). She refused to believe that my gums were temporarily inflamed (my lips/gums became inflamed over the last 2 days but it is not something I usually struggle with). She was messy and left my mouth covered in white, sticky pieces of fluoride without explaining whether that was normal or not. At one point, she asked whether she had accidentally removed my filling while scraping my tooth.

Very disappointed and wish that Tend would have taken better care to pair me with an experienced hygienist on my first visit. Unfortunately left a poor impression. I almost left during the middle of the visit.

Also, the fluoride treatment left a strange and terribly ugly white residue on my teeth - my teeth normally never have these dirty-looking white patches!!
